# Card Primitives Only

When implementing card UI in this repo, use primitives from `@workspace/ui/components/card` and avoid custom `div`-based card shells.

- Prefer `CardFrame` for grouped/stacked card sections.
- Use `Card`, `CardHeader`, `CardTitle`, `CardAction`, `CardPanel`, and `CardFooter` for card structure.
- Reuse existing card composition patterns from nearby components before creating new layout wrappers.
- Do not build card shells with ad-hoc `div` containers plus utility classes to imitate card borders, shadows, or padding.
- Keep custom `div` usage inside card content only (for layout of fields/media), not for the card container itself.

## Preferred pattern

```tsx
<Card>
  <CardHeader>
    <CardTitle>Title</CardTitle>
    <CardAction>{/* actions */}</CardAction>
  </CardHeader>
  <CardPanel>{/* content */}</CardPanel>
</Card>
```
